      "writtenOn": "2020-12-16T15:23:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "+Nodir\n\nI don\u0027t grasp BB final status values either. Why does it follow this formula?\n  f(n) :\u003d (1\u003c\u003cended_bits) + (1\u003c\u003c(ended_bits+n))   for n \u003e 0\n\nUnless I\u0027m missing some additional benefit in the above, I\u0027d prefer simpler:\nENDED_THRESHOLD \u003d 64 // allow ~62 non-final statuses.\nENDED_MASK \u003d 64 // works as mask, too.\nFAILED \u003d 64+1\nCANCELLED \u003d 64+2\n// we can add ~60 more w/o exceeding 1 byte on the wire (127 is max in varint encoding)",
